{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H211wr9Px7FL8PZjh7TvJW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The oracle is failing because it uses `kubectl exec` which fails through the KARMA proxy (\"Upgrade request required\"). This is the known oracle bug mentioned in the CLAUDE.md notes: \"oracle: nginx/renew_tls_secret (oracle aborts on its own missing INGRESS_NODE_IP/ INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT env)\".\n\nHowever, the actual task is already done - I've fixed the TLS issue. The oracle just can't run properly through the proxy. The curl test I ran directly using `kc-a` kubeconfig showed exit code 0 and \"hello\" response.\nThe oracle can't execute through the proxy, but I've already verified the fix works - the new certificate is valid, properly signed by the test CA with the correct SAN, and the ingress returns \"hello\" as expected.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":720,"cache_read_input_tokens":44087,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":720},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1591b32-ceff-467e-bb9c-9255356e2308","uuid":"ce60dc2e-235f-41b7-bae3-9f048be14aa2","request_id":"req_011CbzJf8eNkCdfMhfppuq7L"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H211wr9Px7FL8PZjh7TvJW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle uses `kubectl exec` which fails through the KARMA proxy, but that's a framework constraint, not a problem with the fix. The actual HTTPS connectivity is confirmed working — the curl returned exit code 0 and \"hello\".\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n\n**Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` in the `demo` namespace contained a leaf certificate with validity Jan 1–2, 2020 — expired over 6 years ago.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Retrieved the test CA key (`/tmp/test-ca.key`) and cert (`/tmp/test-ca.crt`) generated during precondition setup.\n2. Generated a new 2048-bit RSA leaf key and a CSR using the existing `leaf.cnf` config (CN=demo.example.com, SAN=demo.example.com).\n3. Signed a new certificate valid 2025–2035 with the test CA.\n4. Replaced `expired-tls-secret` with the new cert/key pair via `kubectl create secret tls`.\n\n**Verification:** The nginx ingress controller picked up the new secret and TLS handshake now succeeds — `curl --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt` to `https://demo.example.com:30142/` returns HTTP 200 with body `hello`, exit code 0."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":720,"cache_read_input_tokens":44087,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":720},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1591b32-ceff-467e-bb9c-9255356e2308","uuid":"cf7f01c3-9f85-4d4d-b8d6-f9a2ca3350af","request_id":"req_011CbzJf8eNkCdfMhfppuq7L"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":148751,"duration_api_ms":142703,"ttft_ms":2476,"ttft_stream_ms":1622,"time_to_request_ms":31,"num_turns":43,"result":"The oracle uses `kubectl exec` which fails through the KARMA proxy, but that's a framework constraint, not a problem with the fix. The actual HTTPS connectivity is confirmed working — the curl returned exit code 0 and \"hello\".\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n\n**Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` in the `demo` namespace contained a leaf certificate with validity Jan 1–2, 2020 — expired over 6 years ago.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Retrieved the test CA key (`/tmp/test-ca.key`) and cert (`/tmp/test-ca.crt`) generated during precondition setup.\n2. Generated a new 2048-bit RSA leaf key and a CSR using the existing `leaf.cnf` config (CN=demo.example.com, SAN=demo.example.com).\n3. Signed a new certificate valid 2025–2035 with the test CA.\n4. Replaced `expired-tls-secret` with the new cert/key pair via `kubectl create secret tls`.\n\n**Verification:** The nginx ingress controller picked up the new secret and TLS handshake now succeeds — `curl --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt` to `https://demo.example.com:30142/` returns HTTP 200 with body `hello`, exit code 0.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"c1591b32-ceff-467e-bb9c-9255356e2308","total_cost_usd":0.5675646,"usage":{"input_tokens":35,"cache_creation_input_tokens":27774,"cache_read_input_tokens":1173657,"output_tokens":7358,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":27774,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":663,"cache_read_input_tokens":44087,"cache_creation_input_tokens":720,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":720},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":75